President Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of Mississippi due to severe storms, flooding, and tornadoes that occurred from December 27 to December 28, 2019. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available to state and eligible local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Additionally, federal funding will be available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Jon K. Huss has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and supported by damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.